  "response": "Okay, I can definitely try! To help me identify the music video, please provide me with as much information as possible. The more details you give, the better my chances of figuring it out. Here's a breakdown of things that would be useful:\n\n**Visual Details:**\n\n*   **Description of the artist(s):** Male, female, group, ethnicity, style of dress, hair color, instruments they play.\n*   **Genre:** Is it pop, rock, hip-hop, R&B, electronic, country, indie, metal, classical, etc.?\n*   **Setting/Location:** Where does the video take place? (e.g., a club, a beach, a city street, a desert, a fantasy world, space, inside a house, a stage). Is it brightly lit, dark, colorful, black and white?\n*   **Plot/Storyline:** What happens in the video? Is there a narrative? Are there specific actions, events, or recurring images? Is it abstract or literal?\n*   **Special Effects/Visuals:** Are there any notable special effects, animation, or unique visual elements?\n*   **Era/Time Period (approximate):** When do you think the video was released? (e.g., 80s, 90s, early 2000s, recent).\n*   **Overall Mood/Vibe:** Is it happy, sad, serious, funny, romantic, dark, energetic, surreal?\n\n**Auditory Details:**\n\n*   **Lyrics/Phrases:** Do you remember any specific lyrics or phrases from the song? Even a few words can be helpful.\n*   **Vocal Style:** Male or female vocals? Solo or group vocals? High-pitched, low-pitched, raspy, etc.?\n*   **Instrumentation:** What instruments are prominent in the song? (e.g., guitar, piano, drums, synthesizer, strings).\n*   **Tempo:** Is the song fast, slow, or medium-paced?\n*   **Melody:** Can you describe the melody (e.g., catchy, melancholic, upbeat)? Even humming a few notes (if you can record it somehow) could be useful.\n\n**Other Information:**\n\n*   **Where did you see the video?** (e.g., MTV, YouTube, a friend's house, a specific website).\n*   **When did you see the video?** (approximate year or time period).\n*   **Anything else you remember!** Even seemingly insignificant details might be the key to identifying the video.\n\n**Example:**\n\n\"I'm trying to find a music video I saw in the early 2000s. It was a pop song by a female artist with blonde hair. The video was set in a high school, and she was singing in the cafeteria. There were cheerleaders and football players in the background. I think the song was about heartbreak or being left out.\"\n\n**The more you tell me, the better I can help!** I'll do my best to figure it out based on your description.",
